author: The Piano Guys
description:
Ordinary has struck a chord with so many people, and we felt its message deserved a simple, heartfelt tribute. This piano and cello version is our way of honoring the raw emotion and honesty Alex Warren brings to the original. Just two instruments, carrying the weight of something deeply human.

author: The Piano Guys
description:
“Just a piano, for a story that soars.”
This simple piano version of Test Drive is our quiet tribute to the wonder of How to Train Your Dragon. The music has always moved us, and this arrangement is our way of honoring the spirit of adventure, friendship, and flight that makes the story so unforgettable.

author: The Piano Guys
description:
Composed in 1982 while Jon Schmidt was still in high school, this piece began as a simple entry for the Reflections music contest. Encouraged by a teacher and driven by a desire to make him proud, Jon chose a song that was easy to transcribe, and unexpectedly landed upon this piece.
